I have been to this place many times before and their pizza is good.. But today was very troubling to me as i went in and told the guy behind the counter my order  i was on my phone so i really didn't make that much eye contact with the guy who put my order in the oven i just paid for the pizza's he handed to me and sat down to eat. When i finished my pizzas and got up i looked over to the guy to say thank you and thats when i saw he had many large opened uncovered wounds all over his arms neck face and the back of his hands, i was shocked and also disgusted to see that because i ate the food he gave me and he was behind the counter handing people their food.... My question is? Is that not a violation under the health code....?    Im very very disappointed because i really liked that place..

I remember being a seven-year-old watching them toss pizza dough and even taking class trips for learning how to create pizza. I'm really thrilled that this place is still around now that I'm in my thirties, although the location and set up has changed (I will forever miss the viewing counter on 7th Ave). I dare you to find a place with bigger portions for as reasonable a price as you find here. My one critique is I wish you guys would expand your vegan menu and update your pizza. The pre-made daiya cheese used for the vegan cheese is awful and I've no doubt that people in the kitchen could cook something better from scratch.

Whats not to love about two boots? Maybe the prices.... But its worth it. My Bff and I always make our own pie with shrimp, crawfish, mushrooms, and fresh garlic. Heavenly!!! (Not for the kids) Hilarious! Go and grab a pie and some beets with friends. You won't regret it.
